OL,3,CNo 10 criticises London theatre's
OL,4,C'divisive' plans for black-only nights
OL,6,F"We will release further details soon.
OL,7,FTo be absolutely clear, no one will be
OL,8,Fprevented or precluded from attending
OL,9,Fany performance of Slave Play."
OL,11,FOn Thursday, Prime Minister Rishi
OL,12,FSunak's official spokesman said: "The
OL,13,Fprime minister is a big supporter of
OL,14,Fthe arts and he believes that the arts
OL,15,Fshould be inclusive and open to
OL,16,Feveryone, particularly where those
OL,17,Farts venues are in receipt of public
OL,18,Ffunding.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@_O]tD@bOU
